laboratory_examinations.findings: The appendix is dilated and fluid-filled measuring 1.5 cm in dimension with surrounding inflammatory changes and thickening of the lateroconal fascia compatible with acute complicated appendicitis. No focal lesion in the liver, no intrahepatic biliary ductal dilatation, patent portal vein, unremarkable gallbladder, pancreas, spleen, bilateral adrenal glands, kidneys, stomach, duodenum, loops of small bowel, cecum, and colon. Trace abdominal free fluid noted.
